  <Language_en_US>
	  <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_TB_MILITARY_FACTORY">
		  <Text>Military Factory</Text>
	  </Row>
	  <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_BUILDINGS_TB_MILITARY_FACTORY_TEXT">
		  <Text>
			  A military factory is a building which uses Industrial Age techniques to build military equipment, arms and ammunitions, and vehicles. First appearing in a large scale in the 17th and 18th centuries, military factories were more efficient than the small workshops or cottage industries they replaced.
		  </Text>
	  </Row>
	  <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_TB_MILITARY_FACTORY_STRATEGY">
		  <Text>The Military Factory is an Industrial-era building which greatly increases a city's [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production. The city must already possess a Workshop (or Longhouse). 1 [ICON_RES_COAL] Coal is consumed when a Military Factory is created.</Text>
	  </Row>
	  <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_TB_MILITARY_FACTORY_HELP">
		  <Text>+20 XP for all Units and 25% [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production when building Armored Units.</Text>
	  </Row>
  </Language_en_US>
